<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="466" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,749,1350]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,749,774]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male. In the group VII key of 
<bibRefCitation author="Borgmeier" box="[632,836,749,774]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" refString="Borgmeier, T. (1966) Revision of the North American phorid flies. Part III. The species of the genus Megaselia, subgenus Megaselia. Studia Entomologica, 8, 1 - 160." type="journal article" year="1966">
Borgmeier (
<number box="[768,828,749,774]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" value="1966.0">1966</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[850,991,750,773]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marquezi">
<emphasis box="[850,991,750,773]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">M. marquezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
keys to 
<taxonomicName authority="Borgmeier" authorityName="Borgmeier" box="[1091,1369,749,774]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundula">
<emphasis box="[1091,1240,749,773]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">M. rotundula</emphasis>
Borgmeier
</taxonomicName>
, from which it differs by having 
<number box="[450,464,786,810]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" value="3.0">3</number>
notopleural setae rather than the 
<number box="[841,855,786,810]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" value="2.0">2</number>
found on 
<taxonomicName box="[971,1118,785,809]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundula">
<emphasis box="[971,1118,785,809]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">M. rotundula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and by the lack of a hair at the base of R (
<taxonomicName box="[314,460,821,845]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Megaselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundula">
<emphasis box="[314,460,821,845]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">M. rotundula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a long, conspicuous hair).
</paragraph>
